## Day 2: Waking up

It's about 8am in the morning when you realize you're not sleeping any more. Your whole body hurts. Yesterday, you used and abused muscles that you haven't needed for the last several years. You slowly sit up and look out the window. It's a nice view down the street, the calming green of your neighbours' front gardens being a much better sight than the bedroom's interior.

There's something strange going on outside today, though. Two cars are parked in the middle of the road, and two men with baseball bats are quietly talking to each other over the roof of one of them.

