Maria Car: run

You are too confused and tired to think about the best possible route of escape, so you pick a side randomly and start running along the road. You quickly realize how stupid this is, running from a car along a road, and you can also hear the Mazda rolling on idle a few paces behind you.

You decide to jump over a fence into someone's front yard, but that's when your legs give in and you land on your knees, breathing in and out so quickly it hurts. Hyperventilation. That's the scientific term for it. There are many causes of hyperventilation, you have been taught, including strokes and various lung diseases, but mostly it's caused by something much less glorious. A panic attack.

As the red Mazda slowly pulls over at your side, you manage to persuade your mind to calm down a bit, and you consciously slow down your breath. By the time Maria Pruitt slides her side window down, you are able to stand up, breathe normally, and talk.

